:: Public Holidays

: Enkutatash (New Year)
"Enkutatash"                                       public on ethiopian meskerem 1
: Meskel (Discovery of the True Cross)
"Meskel"                                           public religious on ethiopian meskerem 17
: Genna (Christmas)
"Genna"                                            public religious on ethiopian tahsas 29
: Timkat (Epiphany)
"Timkat"                                           public religious on ethiopian ter 11
: Adwa Victory Day
"Adwa Victory Day"                                 public commemorative on ethiopian yakatit 23
: Patriots' Victory Day
"Patriots' Victory Day"                            public commemorative on ethiopian miyazya 27
: Downfall of the Derg
"Downfall of the Derg"                             public commemorative on ethiopian genbot 20

: Sikilet (Good Friday)
"Sikilet"                                          public religious on pascha minus 2 days
: Fasika (Easter Sunday)
"Fasika"                                           public religious on pascha

: International Workers' Day
"International Workers' Day"                       public on may 1

: Eid al-Fitr (End of Ramadan)
"Eid al-Fitr"                                      public religious on hijri shawwal 1 length 3
: Eid al-Adha (Feast of Sacrifice)
"Eid al-Adha"                                      public religious on hijri thualhijjah 10 length 3
: Mawlid (Prophet's Birthday)
"Mawlid"                                           public religious on hijri rabialawal 12
